# Copy to `.env` and adjust. Every var here is OPTIONAL — the defaults are what production uses.
#
# Heads up: the backend is a separate, private repo, so a clean clone of this repository cannot run
# the app end to end. The UI, offline queue, and PWA are all here; the API is not. See README.

# Where the API lives.
#   unset/empty -> same-origin. This is what production does: a custom server entry forwards
#                  /api/v1/spendoff/* to the backend over a Cloudflare service binding, keeping
#                  cookies first-party and avoiding CORS.
#   in dev      -> also leave this empty. vite.config.ts proxies /api/v1/spendoff/* to
#                  http://localhost:8787 for you.
#   set         -> calls the backend cross-origin. Needs CORS + credentials configured there.
# VITE_API_BASE=http://localhost:8787

# Overrides the app title. Purely cosmetic.
# VITE_APP_TITLE=Spendoff

# Absolute origin of the deployed app; used for server-side URL building.
# SERVER_URL=https://spendoff.us
